
@startuml

class School {
  -name: String
  -principal: Teacher
  -rooms: Set<Room>
  -classGroups: Set<ClassGroup>
}

class Teacher {
  -firstName: String
  -lastName: String
  -email: String
  -schools: Set<School>
  -teachingHours: Map<School, Integer>
}

class Student {
  -firstName: String
  -lastName: String
  -school: School
  -classGroup: ClassGroup
}

class Room {
  -name: String
  -capacity: Integer
  -size: Integer
  -type: String
}

class ClassGroup {
  -name: String
  -students: Set<Student>
  -room: Room
}

School "1" -- "1" ClassGroup : has
ClassGroup "1" -- "1" Room : assigned to
Student "1" -- "1" ClassGroup : belongs to
Student "1" -- "1" School : attends
Teacher "1" -- "*" School : teaches at
Teacher "1" -- "1" ClassGroup : ? (optional)
School "1" -- "1" Teacher : principal
Teacher "1" -- "1" School : principal of

@enduml

### Explanation of Relationships:
- **School** has a **principal** who is a **Teacher**.
- A **Teacher** can teach at multiple **Schools**, with the number of hours recorded.
- A **Teacher** can only be the **principal** of one **School**.
- A **Student** belongs to exactly one **ClassGroup** and attends exactly one **School**.
- A **ClassGroup** is assigned to exactly one **Room** and contains between 10 and 31 **Students**.
- **Rooms** can be of different types (e.g., classroom, gym), but all have a **name**, **capacity** (for classrooms), or **size** (for other rooms).

